00:17:54.510 --> 00:18:06.040
[ Music ]

00:18:06.040 --> 00:18:11.230
So, I do that slow as I
can and then they listen,

00:18:11.230 --> 00:18:14.610
so that I can get them
familiarized with the melody.

00:18:14.610 --> 00:18:16.040
I say this is how the melody go.

00:18:16.040 --> 00:18:17.920
And I say -- it's only two keys,

00:18:17.920 --> 00:18:19.930
it's just back and
forth, G, D7, G, D7.

00:18:19.930 --> 00:18:22.360
And that's all you use.

00:18:22.360 --> 00:18:25.580
And I say, you listen
how the melody go.

00:18:25.580 --> 00:18:30.340 position:56%
So, I said, "Now, take your camera
and I play the whole song for them."

00:18:30.340 --> 00:18:34.970
After the whole song is done and
then part from one to two and --

00:18:34.970 --> 00:18:39.820
and by the end of the class
