rest, because it's not on paper.

00:18:49.260 --> 00:18:53.510 position:56%
And the good thing about it is when
they got it, they say, "Mr. Kapana."

00:18:53.510 --> 00:18:54.810
I say, "yes."

00:18:54.810 --> 00:18:56.110
"Oh, we got it."

00:18:56.110 --> 00:18:57.410
Yeah, let me hear it.

00:18:57.410 --> 00:18:59.050
And I hear the -- and
I say, "Oh, good job."

00:18:59.050 --> 00:19:00.350
Let me see.

00:19:00.350 --> 00:19:01.650
They give me the guitar.

00:19:01.650 --> 00:19:05.560
So, I play the song
again and they look at me

00:19:05.560 --> 00:19:07.880
and they say, "Mr. Kaapana."

00:19:07.880 --> 00:19:09.180
I say, "Yes."

00:19:09.180 --> 00:19:10.880
They go, "you didn't
teach us that part."

00:19:10.880 --> 00:19:15.400
So, -- so I'll tell them, oh,
I have to save some for me.

00:19:15.400 --> 00:19:17.410
&gt;&gt;JOHN FENN: So, if someone
watches that video and practices

00:19:17.410 --> 00:19:23.290
for 40 years, they could be okay.

00:19:23.290 --> 00:19:24.590
&gt;&gt;LEDWARD KAAPANA: Yes.

00:19:24.590 --> 00:19:25.890
So, that's the way I teach.

00:19:25.890 --> 00:19:29.400
It's not -- I mean, when I first
started teaching it was real

00:19:29.400 --> 00:19:33.560
stressful for me because I
don't write nothing down.

00:19:33.560 --> 00:19:35.180
because I don't know
how to write down,

00:19:35.180 --> 00:19:37.780
but I just know how to play it.

00:19:37.780 --> 00:19:41.050
So I told -- you know, all
those teachers that teach,

00:19:41.050 --> 00:19:44.970
I try to go to the class, I ask
them, "Can I come see your class?"

00:19:44.970 --> 00:19:46.270
they said no.

00:19:46.270 --> 00:19:48.520
They don't want me to
come to their class.

00:19:48.520 --> 00:19:49.820
They said, you know, they tell me,

00:19:49.820 --> 00:19:51.330
"Why do you want to
come to the class?"

00:19:51.330 --> 00:19:57.110 position:56%
I just want to see how you teach the
student, that's all I want to know.

00:19:57.110 --> 00:20:00.800
And they tell me, "You just
teach them the way you learned."

00:20:00.800 --> 00:20:02.100
And I said, "Really?"

00:20:02.100 --> 00:20:06.780
And there's a gentlemen back
in Hawaii, she's icon too,

00:20:06.780 --> 00:20:10.200
her name is Ozzie Kultonic [assumed
spelling], so I asked Ozzie,

00:20:10.200 --> 00:20:13.500
Ozzie said, "No, Led, you
teach them the way you learned,

00:20:13.500 --> 00:20:14.800
that's the best way."

00:20:14.800 --> 00:20:16.100
I said, "Why?"

00:20:16.100 --> 00:20:17.400
She said, "Because it's from here."

